label.value: resistance to G418

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of G418 than normal.

label.value: resistance to phleomycin

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of phleomycin than normal.

label.value: abolished protein localization to nucleus during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is abolished during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to mitotic spindle during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle does not occur during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to microtubule minus-end

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the minus ends of microtubules is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal regulation of DNA replication initiation

value.value: A regulation phenotype in which regulation of the initiation of DNA-dependent DNA replication is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of DNA replication initiation

value.value: A regulation phenotype in which negative regulation of the initiation of DNA-dependent DNA replication is abnormal. May result in re-replication of all or part of the genome.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of premeiotic DNA replication initiation

value.value: A regulation phenotype in which negative regulation of the initiation of premeiotic DNA replication is abnormal. May result in re-replication of all or part of the genome.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of premeiotic DNA replication initiation resulting in complete rereplication

value.value: A regulation phenotype in which negative regulation of the initiation of premeiotic DNA replication is abnormal, resulting in one or more rounds of rereplication of the entire genome.

label.value: abnormal sporulation resulting in formation of azygotic ascus with more than four spores

value.value: A sporulation phenotype in which azygotic asci that contain more than four, and up to eight, spores form following conjugation, diploid growth, and subsequent azygotic sporulation. Azygotic ascus formation occurs when meiosis takes place within a diploid cell rather than in a zygote produced by sporulation. Zygotes can resume vegetative growth and form colonies of diploid cells if returned to rich media before commitment to meiosis; under nitrogen starvation, diploid cells heterozygous for mating type will undergo azygotic meiosis. Azygotic asci have a characteristic linear morphology resembling that of a single vegetatively growing cell.

label.value: increased histone exchange at pericentric heterochromatin

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone exchange occurs to a greater extent than normal in regions of pericentric heterochromatin. Histone exchange is replacement, within chromatin, of resident histones or histone subunits with alternative, sometimes variant, histones or subunits.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to kinetochore during meiosis

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore is abnormal during one or both meiotic nuclear divisions.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found associated with the kinetochore and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to kinetochore during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome does not occur during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to meiotic spindle pole body during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the meiotic spindle pole body is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal cell population growth during glucose starvation

value.value: A cell growth phenotype in which cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) under conditions of glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: abolished cytoplasmic interphase microtubule nucleation

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of cytoplasmic microtubules from one or both of the normal nucleation sites does not occur during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. Normally, microtubules are nucleated from interphase microtubule organizing centers (iMTOCs) and from the cytoplasmic face of the spindle pole body (SPB).

definition.value: This term can be used if microtubule nucleation is abolished from either the iMTOC or SPB, or from both sites.

label.value: increased vacuolar alanine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-alanine measured in the vacuole is higher than normal.

label.value: increased vacuolar arginine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-arginine measured in the vacuole is higher than normal.

label.value: increased vacuolar asparagine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-asparagine measured in the vacuole is higher than normal.

label.value: increased vacuolar glutamine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-glutamine measured in the vacuole is higher than normal.

label.value: increased vacuolar glycine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of glycine measured in the vacuole is higher than normal.

label.value: increased vacuolar histidine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-histidine measured in the vacuole is higher than normal.

label.value: increased vacuolar lysine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-lysine measured in the vacuole is higher than normal.

label.value: increased vacuolar proline level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-proline measured in the vacuole is higher than normal.

label.value: increased vacuolar serine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-serine measured in the vacuole is higher than normal.

label.value: increased vacuolar threonine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-threonine measured in the vacuole is higher than normal.

label.value: abnormal farnesyltranstransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of farnesyltranstransferase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased farnesyltranstransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of farnesyltranstransferase activity is decreased.

label.value: normal farnesyltranstransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of farnesyltranstransferase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased protein localization to plasma membrane, with protein mislocalized to cytoplasm, during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane is decreased, and some of the protein is present in the cytoplasm instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed onset of mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint begins later than normal under conditions that normally trigger the checkpoint signaling and response. Normally, the mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint negatively regulates progression through the G2/M transition of the cell cycle in response to DNA damage.

label.value: spores resistant to ionizing radiation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which spores germinate to a greater extent than wild type following exposure to ionizing radiation.

label.value: abnormal histone methyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a histone methyltransferase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased histone methyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a histone methyltransferase activity is decreased.

label.value: increased RNA level during cellular response to menadione

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to menadione is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to Golgi apparatus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the Golgi apparatus is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal DNA/DNA annealing activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a DNA/DNA annealing activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: circularized chromosome during mitotic G2 phase

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which telomeres have fused, forming circular chromosomes, during G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: abnormal telomere-nuclear envelope distance during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distance between one or more telomeres and the nuclear envelope is abnormal (i.e. greater or less than the distance in wild type cells).

label.value: increased telomere-nuclear envelope distance during mitotic G2 phase

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distance between one or more telomeres and the nuclear envelope is greater than normal during G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: decreased telomere-nuclear envelope distance during mitotic G2 phase

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distance between one or more telomeres and the nuclear envelope is smaller than normal during G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: decreased telomere-nuclear envelope distance during mitotic M phase

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distance between one or more telomeres and the nuclear envelope is smaller than normal during mitosis.

label.value: normal zygotic meiosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the meiotic nuclear divisions are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cycle of zygotic meiosis and sporulation. Zygotic meiosis and sporulation take place under conditions of continuous nitrogen starvation, in which haploid cells of the opposite mating types conjugate to form diploid zygotes that proceed immediately to undergo meiosis and sporulation.

label.value: normal azygotic meiosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the meiotic nuclear divisions are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cycle of azygotic meiosis and sporulation. Azygotic meiosis and sporulation occur when meiosis takes place within a diploid cell rather than in a zygote produced by sporulation. Zygotes can resume vegetative growth and form colonies of diploid cells if returned to rich media before commitment to meiosis; under nitrogen starvation, diploid cells heterozygous for mating type will undergo azygotic meiosis. Azygotic asci have a characteristic linear morphology resembling that of a single vegetatively growing cell.

label.value: normal azygotic meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the first meiotic nuclear division is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cycle of azygotic meiosis and sporulation. Azygotic meiosis and sporulation occur when meiosis takes place within a diploid cell rather than in a zygote produced by sporulation. Zygotes can resume vegetative growth and form colonies of diploid cells if returned to rich media before commitment to meiosis; under nitrogen starvation, diploid cells heterozygous for mating type will undergo azygotic meiosis. Azygotic asci have a characteristic linear morphology resembling that of a single vegetatively growing cell.

label.value: abolished azygotic meiosis II

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the second meiotic nuclear division does not occur during a cycle of azygotic meiosis and sporulation. Azygotic meiosis and sporulation occur when meiosis takes place within a diploid cell rather than in a zygote produced by sporulation. Zygotes can resume vegetative growth and form colonies of diploid cells if returned to rich media before commitment to meiosis; under nitrogen starvation, diploid cells heterozygous for mating type will undergo azygotic meiosis. Azygotic asci have a characteristic linear morphology resembling that of a single vegetatively growing cell.

label.value: abolished zygotic meiosis II

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the second meiotic nuclear division does not occur during a cycle of zygotic meiosis and sporulation. Zygotic meiosis and sporulation take place under conditions of continuous nitrogen starvation, in which haploid cells of the opposite mating types conjugate to form diploid zygotes that proceed immediately to undergo meiosis and sporulation.

label.value: abolished premeiotic DNA replication during azygotic meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which premeiotic DNA replication does not occur during a cycle of azygotic meiosis and sporulation. Azygotic meiosis and sporulation occur when meiosis takes place within a diploid cell rather than in a zygote produced by sporulation. Zygotes can resume vegetative growth and form colonies of diploid cells if returned to rich media before commitment to meiosis; under nitrogen starvation, diploid cells heterozygous for mating type will undergo azygotic meiosis. Azygotic asci have a characteristic linear morphology resembling that of a single vegetatively growing cell.

label.value: delayed onset of premeiotic DNA replication during azygotic meiosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which premeiotic DNA replication begins later than normal during a cycle of azygotic meiosis and sporulation. Azygotic meiosis and sporulation occur when meiosis takes place within a diploid cell rather than in a zygote produced by sporulation. Zygotes can resume vegetative growth and form colonies of diploid cells if returned to rich media before commitment to meiosis; under nitrogen starvation, diploid cells heterozygous for mating type will undergo azygotic meiosis. Azygotic asci have a characteristic linear morphology resembling that of a single vegetatively growing cell.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to shmoo tip

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the tip of a shmoo, or mating projection, is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
